<br>
They are these two swords: (they are actually very Inu Yasha clad. Like the Tetsusaiga and the Tenseiga. I didn't mean it to be like that, though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :\ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":\"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    )<br>
<br>
Dairyoku- A sword which was created so that one slash of the sword would be equal to the strength of fifty men.<br>
<br>
Daimamori- A sword created so that it would be as strong as fifty men, and never would break.<br>
<br>
Basically, the Dairyoku was the original sword and was created by a sword smith to give to Mamoru's father. After his father past away, along with Shosetsu, both of their graves were robbed. Shosetsu was missing from the grave, and the Dairyoku was missing from Mamoru's father's grave. Shosetsu had taken the sword, and is now going to use it against his brother.<br>
Mamoru (after getting the crap kicked out of him by Shosetsu and the Dairyoku) now heads over to the same old man who crafted the first sword. Mamoru asks him to make a rival sword that can be used against the Dairyoku, and so he makes the Daimamori.<br>
<br>
[Edit:]<br>
One thing I'm having a hard time thinking of, is a reason for Iaka (I called him Akai when I first posted) to be after the girl who hired Mamoru (I gave her a name, Keiko.) I was thinking at first for it to be a money issue, that maybe her father owes him money and Iaka was going to kidnap her to get the money back, but that doesn't work out right. Then I was going to have it that Keiko's father owed him money, and Iaka killed him, now he's after Keiko, but then I though &quot;There's no money in revenge.&quot; So I'm stuck. Pretty much anything to do with money is out of the question because it won't work out...<br>
<br>
